{
  "stem": "2723.3",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I was extremely hurt.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And when we finally arrived in Prague, there was-- probably my ignorance as to how people would handle returnees like me made it bitter, because we were again marshalled and again standing and again waiting for clothes and disinfecting.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I have a piece of paper from the quarantine station in Prague, which was probably hugely necessary, never mind my having had a bath and lived like a semi-human being in Ravensbruck.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But I still had problems.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I still was very sick.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they had to do it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But I resented that much more than I resented anything else.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I finished up in a hospital in Prague, where I met a woman, who was somebody called Flora, who was a nurse there, and who, um-- who really forced me to face life again.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And, um, she was pretty terrific.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Um, It took a while, because in Prague, they discovered that I had TB.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they allowed me to go back on the proviso that, as I had already found out through the Red Cross, my father was alive in Palestine, my paternal uncles were alive and wanted me back, that for my-- my psyche, it would be better to first have some kind of a reunion before I was hospitalized again.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This was terribly organized, I do recall, because I was really very, very weak.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was sent back-- I can't remember whether it was by train, part of the way truck-- and then deposited at the Bratislava railway station, not knowing where they were.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Nobody had notified.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was no communication possible.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My uncle had no idea when I was coming, so he didn't wait for me.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
